    "step1_procedural_posture": "This is an appeal from the United States District Court for the Eastern District of New York. The district court granted the United States Department of Education's motion to dismiss Robert Dingle, Jr.'s amended complaint for lack of subject matter jurisdiction under Rule 12(h)(3). The dismissal was without prejudice. The district court adopted a magistrate judge's Report and Recommendation (R&R) after conducting de novo review in response to timely objections (June 7, 2023 order), and also issued a prior order adopting the R&R for clear error when no objections were filed (April 30, 2023 order). The operative order for appeal is the June 7, 2023 order, as it followed objections.",
